Note: Constraint Management System for AI Agents
Implements comprehensive constraint specification, validation, satisfaction,
optimization, and dynamic constraint handling capabilities
Competitive with constraint programming systems, optimization solvers, and leading constraint frameworks :End Note

Type ConstraintManagementSystem is Dictionary with:
    system id as String
    constraint paradigm as String  Note: "classical", "fuzzy", "temporal", "probabilistic", "hierarchical"
    constraint solvers as List[ConstraintSolver]
    constraint validators as List[ConstraintValidator]
    constraint optimizers as List[ConstraintOptimizer]
    constraint monitors as List[ConstraintMonitor]
    satisfaction engines as List[SatisfactionEngine]
    violation handlers as List[ViolationHandler]
    system configuration as SystemConfiguration

Type ConstraintSolver is Dictionary with:
    solver id as String
    solver type as String  Note: "csp_solver", "smt_solver", "optimization_solver", "logic_solver", "hybrid_solver"
    solving algorithms as List[SolvingAlgorithm]
    search strategies as List[SearchStrategy]
    propagation techniques as List[PropagationTechnique]
    heuristics as List[SolverHeuristic]
    solver performance as SolverPerformance
    solver configuration as SolverConfiguration

Type ConstraintValidator is Dictionary with:
    validator id as String
    validation type as String  Note: "syntactic", "semantic", "consistency", "satisfiability", "completeness"
    validation rules as List[ValidationRule]
    consistency checkers as List[ConsistencyChecker]
    validation algorithms as List[ValidationAlgorithm]
    error detectors as List[ErrorDetector]
    validator performance as ValidatorPerformance

Type Constraint is Dictionary with:
    constraint id as String
    constraint name as String
    constraint type as String  Note: "hard", "soft", "temporal", "resource", "logical", "numeric", "relational"
    constraint scope as ConstraintScope
    constraint variables as List[ConstraintVariable]
    constraint relations as List[ConstraintRelation]
    constraint priority as Integer
    constraint weight as Float
    constraint satisfaction as ConstraintSatisfaction

Type ConstraintVariable is Dictionary with:
    variable id as String
    variable name as String
    variable type as String  Note: "boolean", "integer", "real", "categorical", "temporal", "complex"
    variable domain as VariableDomain
    variable bounds as VariableBounds
    variable dependencies as List[VariableDependency]
    variable constraints as List[VariableConstraint]
    current value as Any
    variable metadata as VariableMetadata

Type ConstraintRelation is Dictionary with:
    relation id as String
    relation type as String  Note: "equality", "inequality", "membership", "temporal", "logical", "functional"
    relation expression as RelationExpression
    relation parameters as RelationParameters
    relation strength as Float
    relation direction as String  Note: "bidirectional", "forward", "backward"
    relation validity as RelationValidity

Type ConstraintSatisfaction is Dictionary with:
    satisfaction id as String
    satisfaction level as Float
    satisfaction status as String  Note: "satisfied", "violated", "partially_satisfied", "unknown"
    satisfaction method as String
    satisfaction confidence as Float
    violation details as ViolationDetails
    satisfaction history as SatisfactionHistory

Type ConstraintProblem is Dictionary with:
    problem id as String
    problem name as String
    problem type as String  Note: "csp", "optimization", "scheduling", "planning", "configuration"
    problem variables as List[ConstraintVariable]
    problem constraints as List[Constraint]
    problem objectives as List[ProblemObjective]
    problem complexity as ProblemComplexity
    problem solution as ProblemSolution

Type ConstraintSolution is Dictionary with:
    solution id as String
    solution variables as Dictionary[String, Any]
    solution quality as SolutionQuality
    solution optimality as String  Note: "optimal", "near_optimal", "feasible", "infeasible"
    solution cost as Float
    solution violations as List[ConstraintViolation]
    solution validation as SolutionValidation
    solution metadata as SolutionMetadata

Type ConstraintViolation is Dictionary with:
    violation id as String
    violated constraint as Constraint
    violation type as String  Note: "hard_violation", "soft_violation", "temporal_violation", "resource_violation"
    violation severity as Float
    violation impact as ViolationImpact
    violation source as ViolationSource
    repair suggestions as List[RepairSuggestion]

Type ConstraintOptimizer is Dictionary with:
    optimizer id as String
    optimization type as String  Note: "single_objective", "multi_objective", "dynamic", "robust", "stochastic"
    optimization algorithms as List[OptimizationAlgorithm]
    objective functions as List[ObjectiveFunction]
    optimization strategies as List[OptimizationStrategy]
    convergence criteria as List[ConvergenceCriterion]
    optimizer performance as OptimizerPerformance

Type ViolationHandler is Dictionary with:
    handler id as String
    handling strategy as String  Note: "repair", "relax", "ignore", "escalate", "adaptive"
    repair mechanisms as List[RepairMechanism]
    relaxation policies as List[RelaxationPolicy]
    escalation procedures as List[EscalationProcedure]
    handler effectiveness as HandlerEffectiveness
    handler configuration as HandlerConfiguration

Note: Constraint Management Engine
Process called "create_constraint_management_system" that takes config as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let constraint_system be create_constraint_system_structure
    Set constraint_system with key "system_id" to generate_constraint_system_id
    Set constraint_system with key "constraint_paradigm" to config with key "paradigm" or "hierarchical"
    Set constraint_system with key "real_time_solving" to config with key "real_time" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "dynamic_constraints" to config with key "dynamic" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "multi_objective_optimization" to config with key "multi_objective" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "distributed_solving" to config with key "distributed" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "uncertainty_handling" to config with key "uncertainty" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "temporal_reasoning" to config with key "temporal" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "soft_constraints" to config with key "soft_constraints" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "violation_recovery" to config with key "violation_recovery" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "adaptive_solving" to config with key "adaptive" or true
    Set constraint_system with key "performance_optimization" to config with key "optimization" or true
    
    Note: Initialize constraint solvers
    Let constraint_solvers be initialize_constraint_solvers with config
    Set constraint_system with key "constraint_solvers" to constraint_solvers
    
    Note: Initialize constraint validators
    Let constraint_validators be initialize_constraint_validators with config
    Set constraint_system with key "constraint_validators" to constraint_validators
    
    Note: Initialize constraint optimizers
    Let constraint_optimizers be initialize_constraint_optimizers with config
    Set constraint_system with key "constraint_optimizers" to constraint_optimizers
    
    Note: Initialize constraint monitors
    Let constraint_monitors be initialize_constraint_monitors with config
    Set constraint_system with key "constraint_monitors" to constraint_monitors
    
    Note: Initialize satisfaction engines
    Let satisfaction_engines be initialize_satisfaction_engines with config
    Set constraint_system with key "satisfaction_engines" to satisfaction_engines
    
    Note: Initialize violation handlers
    Let violation_handlers be initialize_violation_handlers with config
    Set constraint_system with key "violation_handlers" to violation_handlers
    
    Return constraint_system

Process called "solve_constraint_problem" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and problem_context as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let solving_result be empty dictionary
    Set solving_result with key "solving_id" to generate_solving_id
    Set solving_result with key "solving_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    
    Let constraint_problem be problem_context with key "constraint_problem"
    Let solving_strategy be problem_context with key "strategy"
    Let solving_constraints be problem_context with key "constraints"
    Let optimization_objectives be problem_context with key "objectives"
    
    Note: Phase 1: Validate constraint problem
    Let problem_validation_result be validate_constraint_problem with constraint_system and constraint_problem
    Set solving_result with key "problem_validation" to problem_validation_result
    
    If problem_validation_result with key "valid" is not equal to true:
        Set solving_result with key "solving_status" to "validation_failed"
        Set solving_result with key "validation_errors" to problem_validation_result with key "errors"
        Return solving_result
    
    Note: Phase 2: Select appropriate solver
    Let solver_selection_result be select_constraint_solver with constraint_system and constraint_problem and solving_strategy
    Set solving_result with key "solver_selection" to solver_selection_result
    
    Note: Phase 3: Preprocess constraint problem
    Let preprocessing_result be preprocess_constraint_problem with constraint_system and constraint_problem and solver_selection_result
    Set solving_result with key "preprocessing" to preprocessing_result
    
    Note: Phase 4: Apply constraint solving
    Let constraint_solving_result be apply_constraint_solving with constraint_system and preprocessing_result and solving_strategy
    Set solving_result with key "constraint_solving" to constraint_solving_result
    
    Note: Phase 5: Validate solution
    Let solution_validation_result be validate_constraint_solution with constraint_system and constraint_solving_result and constraint_problem
    Set solving_result with key "solution_validation" to solution_validation_result
    
    Note: Phase 6: Optimize solution if needed
    If optimization_objectives is not equal to null:
        Let optimization_result be optimize_constraint_solution with constraint_system and constraint_solving_result and optimization_objectives
        Set solving_result with key "optimization" to optimization_result
    
    Note: Phase 7: Handle violations if any
    Let violation_handling_result be handle_constraint_violations with constraint_system and solving_result
    Set solving_result with key "violation_handling" to violation_handling_result
    
    Return solving_result

Process called "validate_constraint_problem" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and constraint_problem as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let validation_result be empty dictionary
    Set validation_result with key "validation_method" to "comprehensive_constraint_problem_validation"
    
    Let problem_variables be constraint_problem with key "problem_variables"
    Let problem_constraints be constraint_problem with key "problem_constraints"
    Let constraint_validators be constraint_system with key "constraint_validators"
    
    Let validation_errors be empty list
    Let validation_warnings be empty list
    
    Note: Validate variable definitions
    For each variable in problem_variables:
        Let variable_validation be validate_constraint_variable with variable and constraint_validators and constraint_system
        
        If variable_validation with key "valid"] is not equal to true:
            Let variable_errors be variable_validation with key "errors"
            For each error in variable_errors:
                Add error to validation_errors
        
        If variable_validation with key "warnings" is not equal to null:
            Let variable_warnings be variable_validation with key "warnings"
            For each warning in variable_warnings:
                Add warning to validation_warnings
    
    Note: Validate constraint definitions
    For each constraint in problem_constraints:
        Let constraint_validation be validate_individual_constraint with constraint and problem_variables and constraint_validators and constraint_system
        
        If constraint_validation with key "valid" is not equal to true:
            Let constraint_errors be constraint_validation with key "errors"
            For each error in constraint_errors:
                Add error to validation_errors
    
    Note: Check constraint consistency
    Let consistency_validation be check_constraint_consistency with problem_constraints and problem_variables and constraint_system
    Set validation_result with key "consistency_validation" to consistency_validation
    
    If consistency_validation with key "consistent" is not equal to true:
        Let consistency_errors be consistency_validation with key "consistency_errors"
        For each error in consistency_errors:
            Add error to validation_errors
    
    Note: Check problem satisfiability
    Let satisfiability_check be check_problem_satisfiability with constraint_problem and constraint_system
    Set validation_result with key "satisfiability_check" to satisfiability_check
    
    Set validation_result with key "validation_errors" to validation_errors
    Set validation_result with key "validation_warnings" to validation_warnings
    
    If length of validation_errors is equal to 0:
        Set validation_result with key "valid" to true
    Otherwise:
        Set validation_result with key "valid" to false
    
    Return validation_result

Process called "apply_constraint_solving" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and preprocessing_result as Dictionary and solving_strategy as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let solving_result be empty dictionary
    Set solving_result with key "solving_method" to "comprehensive_constraint_solving"
    
    Let preprocessed_problem be preprocessing_result with key "preprocessed_problem"
    Let selected_solver be preprocessing_result with key "selected_solver"
    Let solving_algorithms be selected_solver with key "solving_algorithms"
    
    Let solution_candidates be empty list
    
    Note: Apply multiple solving algorithms
    For each algorithm in solving_algorithms:
        Let algorithm_result be apply_solving_algorithm with algorithm and preprocessed_problem and constraint_system
        
        If algorithm_result with key "solution_found" is equal to true:
            Let candidate_solution be algorithm_result with key "solution"
            Set candidate_solution with key "solving_algorithm" to algorithm with key "algorithm_id"
            Set candidate_solution with key "solving_time" to algorithm_result with key "solving_time"
            Add candidate_solution to solution_candidates
    
    Note: Select best solution
    If length of solution_candidates is greater than 0:
        Let best_solution_selection be select_best_constraint_solution with solution_candidates and solving_strategy and constraint_system
        Set solving_result with key "best_solution" to best_solution_selection with key "selected_solution"
        Set solving_result with key "solution_found" to true
    Otherwise:
        Set solving_result with key "solution_found" to false
        Set solving_result with key "solving_status" to "no_solution_found"
    
    Set solving_result with key "solution_candidates" to solution_candidates
    
    Note: Analyze solving performance
    Let performance_analysis be analyze_constraint_solving_performance with solving_result and constraint_system
    Set solving_result with key "performance_analysis" to performance_analysis
    
    Return solving_result

Process called "handle_constraint_violations" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and solving_result as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let violation_handling be empty dictionary
    Set violation_handling with key "handling_method" to "comprehensive_constraint_violation_handling"
    
    Let solution_validation be solving_result with key "solution_validation"
    Let detected_violations be solution_validation with key "detected_violations"
    Let violation_handlers be constraint_system with key "violation_handlers"
    
    If length of detected_violations is equal to 0:
        Set violation_handling with key "violations_present" to false
        Set violation_handling with key "handling_status" to "no_violations_detected"
        Return violation_handling
    
    Set violation_handling with key "violations_present" to true
    
    Let handled_violations be empty list
    Let unhandled_violations be empty list
    
    Note: Process each violation
    For each violation in detected_violations:
        Let violation_type be violation with key "violation_type"
        Let violation_severity be violation with key "violation_severity"
        
        Note: Select appropriate violation handler
        Let selected_handler be select_violation_handler with violation and violation_handlers and constraint_system
        
        If selected_handler is not equal to null:
            Let handling_attempt be apply_violation_handler with violation and selected_handler and constraint_system
            
            If handling_attempt with key "handling_success" is equal to true:
                Set violation with key "handling_result" to handling_attempt
                Add violation to handled_violations
            Otherwise:
                Set violation with key "handling_failure" to handling_attempt with key "failure_reason"
                Add violation to unhandled_violations
        Otherwise:
            Set violation with key "handling_failure" to "no_suitable_handler_found"
            Add violation to unhandled_violations
    
    Set violation_handling with key "handled_violations" to handled_violations
    Set violation_handling with key "unhandled_violations" to unhandled_violations
    
    Note: Generate repair suggestions for unhandled violations
    If length of unhandled_violations is greater than 0:
        Let repair_suggestions be generate_violation_repair_suggestions with unhandled_violations and constraint_system
        Set violation_handling with key "repair_suggestions" to repair_suggestions
    
    Note: Assess overall handling effectiveness
    Let handling_effectiveness be assess_violation_handling_effectiveness with violation_handling and constraint_system
    Set violation_handling with key "handling_effectiveness" to handling_effectiveness
    
    Return violation_handling

Process called "optimize_constraint_solution" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and constraint_solving_result as Dictionary and optimization_objectives as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let optimization_result be empty dictionary
    Set optimization_result with key "optimization_method" to "comprehensive_constraint_solution_optimization"
    
    Let current_solution be constraint_solving_result with key "best_solution"
    Let constraint_optimizers be constraint_system with key "constraint_optimizers"
    Let objective_functions be optimization_objectives with key "objective_functions"
    Let optimization_constraints be optimization_objectives with key "optimization_constraints"
    
    Note: Select appropriate optimizer
    Let optimizer_selection be select_constraint_optimizer with objective_functions and constraint_optimizers and constraint_system
    Set optimization_result with key "optimizer_selection" to optimizer_selection
    
    Let selected_optimizer be optimizer_selection with key "selected_optimizer"
    
    Note: Apply optimization algorithms
    Let optimization_execution be apply_constraint_optimization_algorithms with current_solution and selected_optimizer and objective_functions and constraint_system
    Set optimization_result with key "optimization_execution" to optimization_execution
    
    Note: Validate optimized solution
    Let optimized_solution_validation be validate_optimized_constraint_solution with optimization_execution and optimization_constraints and constraint_system
    Set optimization_result with key "solution_validation" to optimized_solution_validation
    
    Note: Compare with original solution
    Let solution_comparison be compare_constraint_solutions with current_solution and optimization_execution with key "optimized_solution" and constraint_system
    Set optimization_result with key "solution_comparison" to solution_comparison
    
    Note: Select final solution
    Let final_solution_selection be select_final_optimized_solution with solution_comparison and optimization_objectives and constraint_system
    Set optimization_result with key "final_solution" to final_solution_selection
    
    Return optimization_result

Process called "monitor_constraint_satisfaction" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and monitoring_context as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let monitoring_result be empty dictionary
    Set monitoring_result with key "monitoring_id" to generate_monitoring_id
    Set monitoring_result with key "monitoring_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    
    Let monitored_constraints be monitoring_context with key "constraints"
    Let monitoring_duration be monitoring_context with key "duration"
    Let monitoring_frequency be monitoring_context with key "frequency"
    Let constraint_monitors be constraint_system with key "constraint_monitors"
    
    Let monitoring_data be empty list
    Let satisfaction_violations be empty list
    
    Note: Continuous constraint monitoring loop
    Let current_time be current_timestamp
    Let end_time be current_time plus monitoring_duration
    
    While current_time is less than end_time:
        Let monitoring_snapshot be create_constraint_monitoring_snapshot with current_time
        
        Note: Check satisfaction status for each constraint
        For each constraint in monitored_constraints:
            Let satisfaction_check be check_constraint_satisfaction with constraint and constraint_monitors and constraint_system
            Set monitoring_snapshot with key constraint with key "constraint_id" to satisfaction_check
            
            If satisfaction_check with key "satisfaction_status" is equal to "violated":
                Let violation_record be create_violation_record with constraint and satisfaction_check and current_time
                Add violation_record to satisfaction_violations
        
        Add monitoring_snapshot to monitoring_data
        
        Note: Wait for next monitoring cycle
        Set current_time to current_time plus monitoring_frequency
    
    Set monitoring_result with key "monitoring_data" to monitoring_data
    Set monitoring_result with key "satisfaction_violations" to satisfaction_violations
    
    Note: Analyze monitoring trends
    Let trend_analysis be analyze_constraint_satisfaction_trends with monitoring_data and constraint_system
    Set monitoring_result with key "trend_analysis" to trend_analysis
    
    Note: Generate monitoring report
    Let monitoring_report be generate_constraint_monitoring_report with monitoring_result and constraint_system
    Set monitoring_result with key "monitoring_report" to monitoring_report
    
    Return monitoring_result

Process called "manage_dynamic_constraints" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and dynamic_context as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let dynamic_management be empty dictionary
    Set dynamic_management with key "management_method" to "comprehensive_dynamic_constraint_management"
    Set dynamic_management with key "management_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    
    Let current_constraints be dynamic_context with key "current_constraints"
    Let constraint_changes be dynamic_context with key "constraint_changes"
    Let management_strategy be dynamic_context with key "strategy"
    
    Note: Process constraint changes
    Let change_processing be process_constraint_changes with constraint_changes and current_constraints and constraint_system
    Set dynamic_management with key "change_processing" to change_processing
    
    Note: Update constraint set
    Let constraint_update be update_dynamic_constraint_set with change_processing and current_constraints and constraint_system
    Set dynamic_management with key "constraint_update" to constraint_update
    
    Note: Validate updated constraints
    Let updated_validation be validate_updated_constraint_set with constraint_update and constraint_system
    Set dynamic_management with key "updated_validation" to updated_validation
    
    Note: Propagate constraint changes
    Let change_propagation be propagate_constraint_changes with constraint_update and constraint_system
    Set dynamic_management with key "change_propagation" to change_propagation
    
    Note: Update solutions if needed
    Let solution_update be update_solutions_for_dynamic_constraints with change_propagation and constraint_system
    Set dynamic_management with key "solution_update" to solution_update
    
    Return dynamic_management

Process called "perform_constraint_relaxation" that takes constraint_system as Dictionary and relaxation_context as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let relaxation_result be empty dictionary
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxation_method" to "systematic_constraint_relaxation"
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxation_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    
    Let hard_constraints be relaxation_context with key "hard_constraints"
    Let soft_constraints be relaxation_context with key "soft_constraints"
    Let relaxation_strategy be relaxation_context with key "strategy"
    Let relaxation_limits be relaxation_context with key "limits"
    
    Note: Analyze relaxation requirements
    Let relaxation_analysis be analyze_constraint_relaxation_requirements with hard_constraints and soft_constraints and constraint_system
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxation_analysis" to relaxation_analysis
    
    Note: Generate relaxation candidates
    Let relaxation_candidates be generate_constraint_relaxation_candidates with relaxation_analysis and relaxation_strategy and constraint_system
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxation_candidates" to relaxation_candidates
    
    Note: Evaluate relaxation options
    Let relaxation_evaluation be evaluate_constraint_relaxation_options with relaxation_candidates and relaxation_limits and constraint_system
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxation_evaluation" to relaxation_evaluation
    
    Note: Select optimal relaxation
    Let relaxation_selection be select_optimal_constraint_relaxation with relaxation_evaluation and constraint_system
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxation_selection" to relaxation_selection
    
    Note: Apply constraint relaxation
    Let relaxation_application be apply_constraint_relaxation with relaxation_selection and hard_constraints and soft_constraints and constraint_system
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxation_application" to relaxation_application
    
    Note: Validate relaxed problem
    Let relaxed_validation be validate_relaxed_constraint_problem with relaxation_application and constraint_system
    Set relaxation_result with key "relaxed_validation" to relaxed_validation
    
    Return relaxation_result

Note: Main constraint management system coordination
Process called "create_constraint_management_monitoring_system" that takes configuration as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let system be empty dictionary
    Set system with key "constraint_paradigm" to configuration with key "paradigm" or "hierarchical"
    Set system with key "real_time_solving" to configuration with key "real_time" or true
    Set system with key "dynamic_constraints" to configuration with key "dynamic" or true
    Set system with key "multi_objective_optimization" to configuration with key "multi_objective" or true
    Set system with key "distributed_solving" to configuration with key "distributed" or true
    Set system with key "uncertainty_handling" to configuration with key "uncertainty" or true
    Set system with key "temporal_reasoning" to configuration with key "temporal" or true
    Set system with key "soft_constraints" to configuration with key "soft_constraints" or true
    Set system with key "violation_recovery" to configuration with key "violation_recovery" or true
    Set system with key "adaptive_solving" to configuration with key "adaptive" or true
    Set system with key "performance_optimization" to configuration with key "optimization" or true
    
    Return system

Process called "execute_constraint_management_analysis" that takes system as Dictionary and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let query_type be query with key "type"
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    If query_type is equal to "solve_problem":
        Let problem_context be query with key "problem_context"
        Let solving_config be query with key "solving_config"
        
        Let constraint_system be create_constraint_management_system with solving_config
        Let solving_result be solve_constraint_problem with constraint_system and problem_context
        Set result with key "solving_result" to solving_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "monitor_satisfaction":
        Let monitoring_context be query with key "monitoring_context"
        Let monitoring_config be query with key "monitoring_config"
        
        Let constraint_system be create_constraint_management_system with monitoring_config
        Let monitoring_result be monitor_constraint_satisfaction with constraint_system and monitoring_context
        Set result with key "monitoring_result" to monitoring_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "manage_dynamic":
        Let dynamic_context be query with key "dynamic_context"
        Let dynamic_config be query with key "dynamic_config"
        
        Let constraint_system be create_constraint_management_system with dynamic_config
        Let dynamic_result be manage_dynamic_constraints with constraint_system and dynamic_context
        Set result with key "dynamic_result" to dynamic_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "perform_relaxation":
        Let relaxation_context be query with key "relaxation_context"
        Let relaxation_config be query with key "relaxation_config"
        
        Let constraint_system be create_constraint_management_system with relaxation_config
        Let relaxation_result be perform_constraint_relaxation with constraint_system and relaxation_context
        Set result with key "relaxation_result" to relaxation_result
    
    Note: Add metadata
    Set result with key "constraint_management_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    Set result with key "system_config" to extract_system_summary with system
    
    Return result